Package ohos.bundle

Class InstallParam

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.bundle.InstallParam
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class InstallParam
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Provides parameters required for installing or uninstalling an application.

    The parameters include the user ID and installation mode flag.

    Since:
    1

      • InstallParam

        public InstallParam​(int userId,
                    int installFlag)
        A parameterized constructor used to create an InstallParam instance.

        The value of installFlag is used to specify the installation mode.

        • The value 0 indicates the common installation mode. In this mode, an error will be returned if the package version to be installed for an application is earlier than the existing package version (if any) .
        • The value 1 indicates the overwrite installation mode. In this mode, the package to be installed for an application will always replace the existing package (if any) regardless of whether it is an earlier or later version.
        Parameters:
        userId - Indicates the user ID.
        installFlag - Identifies the installation mode.
        Since:
        1
